    {
      "id": "1a9f7f82_4c3eafc7",
      "file_path": "cps-application/src/main/resources/application.yml",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 164,
      "message": "Using a yaml list here will make it difficult for users to override e.g. you can't override this using an environment variables in a helm chart.\n\nIt would be better to use a string of comma-separated values, and split into a list in the code. We do this for security.permit-uri",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
      "updated": "2024-07-25 12:25:28.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "df8d1b0a_b458981a",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/config/OpenTelemetryConfig.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 114,
      "message": "This is not a task name, it is the observation name. It should really be called 'name' or 'observationName'. (same for excluded-task-names in application.yml, etc.)\n\nYou can use this feature to exclude observations of kafka notifications:\n\n    - spring.kafka.template\n\nor client requests to dmi:\n\n    - http.client.requests",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
      "updated": "2024-07-25 12:25:28.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "87ecb14e_b4870343",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/config/OpenTelemetryConfigProperties.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 34,
      "message": "I'm not convinced it's worth having a separate class for the properties, we we could simply use @Value in the OpenTelemetryConfig class like before:\n\n    @Value(\"${cps.tracing.exporter.endpoint:http://onap-otel-collector:4317}\")\n    private String tracingExporterEndpointUrl;",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
      "updated": "2024-07-25 12:25:28.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "462b3e74_85a5e141",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/config/OpenTelemetryConfigProperties.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 44,
      "message": "If using comma-separated list of names, we could do something like this:\n\n    private String excludedTaskNames;\n\n    @Bean\n    public List<String> excludedTaskNamesList() {\n        return Arrays.asList(excludedTaskNames.split(\",\"));\n    }",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
      "updated": "2024-07-25 12:25:28.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
